Sentencas: Creep damage and creep crack growth (CCG) behavior of Crofer 22 APU as interconnect of solid oxide fuel cell at different temperatures are investigated by the continuum damage mechanics method through CT specimen.
Titulo: Creep fracture behavior of the Crofer 22 APU for the interconnect of solid oxide fuel cell under different temperatures

Sentencas: It is illustrated that the fracture time of CT specimen reduces with temperature increasing at the same stress level, they are 1297 h, 42 h, 1.8 h and 0.25 h, respectively, at 650, 700, 750 and 800 degrees C with stress level of 2.73 MPa.root m. The slopes of creep fracture mechanics parameter C* to CCG rate <(a)over dot> (C*- rate of a) are nearly the same at 650 and 700 degrees
Titulo: Creep fracture behavior of the Crofer 22 APU for the interconnect of solid oxide fuel cell under different temperatures

Sentencas: The slope of C*- <(a)over dot> at 650 and 700 degrees C is smaller than that at 750 and 800 degrees C.
Titulo: Creep fracture behavior of the Crofer 22 APU for the interconnect of solid oxide fuel cell under different temperatures

Sentencas: It is concluded that the temperature effect on CCG behavior of Crofer 22 APU is more evident than that the stress effect.
Titulo: Creep fracture behavior of the Crofer 22 APU for the interconnect of solid oxide fuel cell under different temperatures

Sentencas: All the data of C*- <(a)over dot> fall within the area of 95% prediction band, and the obtained equation of C* and CCG rate is <(a)over dot> = 3.8e2C(*0.91).
